{{DEFAULTSORT:Corel Wordperfect Lightning}}
[[Category:Corel software]]
[[Category:Personal information managers]]


{{Business-software-stub}}

{{italictitle}}
The '''''Corpus Chronicorum Bononiensium''''' is a collection of [[Renaissance]]-era [[chronicle]]s dealing with the history of [[Bologna]].

The collection includes the closely related ''Cronaca Rampona''<ref>*Peter Damian-Grint. "[http://www.encquran.brill.nl/entries/encyclopedia-of-the-medieval-chronicle/cronaca-rampona-SIM_00790 Cronaca Rampona]". Encyclopedia of the Medieval Chronicle. Brill Online, 2013.</ref> and ''Cronaca Varignana''. ''Cronaca Rampona'' was formerly misattributed to Ridolfo Ramponi (whence its conventional title). The text of these chronicles mostly consists of the ''Antichità di Bologna'' by the Franciscan friar Bartolomeo della Pugliola (c. 1358–1422/5), which consists of annalistic down to 1420,<ref>{{emc1|Peter Damian-Grint|Bartolomeo della Pugliola|145-146}}</ref> which in the case of the ''Cronaca Rampona'' was extended in similar style down to the year 1535.

The texts of the collection were edited by [[Albano Sorbelli]] in 1906ff.

